    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-08-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1526.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-08-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 26, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch No. 1025, of the 3d of
                            August, together with a full report of the proceedings in the court of
                            chancery in the case of the cotton claimed by <pb facs="0496" n="456" xml:id="pg_456"/> the United States, has been received, and your
                            action in regard to the matter is approved by this department.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
